# CloudOps Multi-Agent Platform — Local Identity Configuration
# Copy to .env and customize: cp .env.example .env
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# What lives where
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# This file holds ONLY per-developer identity. Shared project settings
# (AWS region, IdP type, cross-account role ARNs, CUR config, deploy
# flags, etc.) live in AWS SSM Parameter Store under
# /$PROJECT_PREFIX/$ENVIRONMENT/config/* and are managed by `make configure`
# / `make reconfigure-shared`. That way every developer pulling the repo
# picks up the same defaults without copying values around.
#
# Flow on a fresh clone:
#   1. cp .env.example .env   # fill in the values below
#   2. make setup              # installs .venv + validates identity
#   3. make configure          # interactive shared-config (writes to SSM)
#   4. make deploy-auto        # deploy the stack
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Required identity
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
PROJECT_PREFIX=cloudops
ENVIRONMENT=dev

# AWS_PROFILE is derived from PROJECT_PREFIX-ENVIRONMENT during `make setup`.
# Set explicitly here only if you need to override that default.
# AWS_PROFILE=cloudops-dev

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auth method (set by `make setup`)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# IAM Identity Center (recommended) vs long-lived access keys. SSO is what the
# setup wizard configures by default — temp creds, browser login, no secrets
# on disk. Switch to "credentials" only if your org doesn't run Identity Center.
AUTH_METHOD=sso

# SSO identity values — these are properties of the human running `make setup`,
# not the deployment, so they live in .env (per-developer) rather than SSM.
#
# SSO_SESSION_NAME is auto-derived as ${PROJECT_PREFIX}-sso so all developers
# on the same deployment share a session name. Don't override unless you know
# what you're doing.
# SSO_SESSION_NAME=cloudops-sso
# SSO_START_URL=https://your-org.awsapps.com/start
# SSO_REGION=us-east-1
# SSO_ACCOUNT_ID=111111111111
# SSO_ROLE_NAME=AdministratorAccess

# Per-target SSO permission-set names — your assigned role in each cross-account
# target. Populated by `make setup` after `make configure` has stored the role
# ARNs in SSM. Leave blank for any target you don't have access to.
# CE_SSO_ROLE_NAME=
# COH_SSO_ROLE_NAME=
# TAG_GOV_SSO_ROLE_NAME=
# HEALTH_SSO_ROLE_NAME=

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Optional per-developer / per-machine overrides
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Any env var set here beats the corresponding SSM value for this user's
# deploys. Useful for one-off testing like deploying a single tool without
# touching the team's shared config.
#
# # Narrow the deploy to one tool for rapid iteration:
# DEPLOY_TOOLS=cost-explorer
#
# # Target a specific agent subset:
# DEPLOY_AGENTS=finops-agent
#
# # Skip the frontend build:
# DEPLOY_MODE=agents-only
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Auto-populated after first deploy (do not set manually)
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# MEMORY_ID is set in SSM (memory/id) — see scripts/deploy.sh post-deploy hook.
# APP_URL is set in SSM (app/url).
